HEADWORD: Cypriniformes
<hw>Cypriniformes</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>an order of fishes including
almost entirely freshwater fishes: characins; loaches; carp; suckers;
sometimes classified as <altname>Cyprinoidea</altname>, a suborder of
<ord>Ostariophysi</ord>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> order <ord>Cypriniformes</ord>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cyprinodont</ent>⟦br⟧
